RESEARCH ANALYST

YouGov is currently recruiting a Research Analyst to work in our Palo Alto office within our Operations department. The successful candidate will work with the Analytics team, which provides project directors  with the operational services they require to offer quality consultancy on a wide variety of topics.

The successful candidate will be provided with the relevant training and support needed to carry out the role.

Responsibilities will include the implementation of house-built software for statistical analysis, including statistical graphics and Web-based delivery.

The ideal candidate should have the following qualifications:

  -- Strong R programming skills

  -- Programming with Python, SQL, C/C++, etc.

  -- Expert with Linux/Unix systems

  -- Commitment and attention to detail and accuracy

  -- Excellent interpersonal, communication, and organizational  skills

  -- Ability to learn new software and techniques

  -- Knowledge of applied statistics is very useful

  -- Familiarity with some or all of discrete choice models, panel data, measurement error, missing data, hierarchical Bayes, survey sampling, factor analysis, structural equation models, experimental design, and data mining very useful

The candidate must have the legal right to work in the United States. Benefits include medical, dental, vision, 401K plan, and Caltrain Go Pass.

Please email jobs.us at yougov.com if you have questions or to apply.

More information and other job opportunities can also be found at http://research.yougov.com/about/careers/




